Comment_contributor: In counting a series eta is used for ‘one;’ eta, rua, oru, &c.
[<tanavuru>, with <n> in italics]; i.e. two the tens, (and) it has come up to two
[<tanafuru>, with <n> in italics]; The sum above both ten and hundred is matara.

Value: i rua taŋarau matara i fai taŋafuru
